What are Ophthalmic Operating Tables?
Ophthalmic Operating Tables are specialized surgical tables designed to provide precise patient positioning, exceptional stability, and seamless integration with advanced ophthalmic surgical equipment during delicate eye procedures. These tables are widely used for cataract surgery, glaucoma surgery, retinal procedures, corneal surgery, and other microsurgical ophthalmic interventions where precision and patient safety are paramount.

Modern ophthalmic operating tables integrate advanced technologies including:

·         Electric Height Adjustment Systems for precise patient positioning

·         Motorized Tilt and Trendelenburg Functions for enhanced surgical accessibility

·         Electro-hydraulic Positioning Mechanisms for smooth and stable movement

·         Integration with Surgical Microscopes and OCT Imaging Systems

·         Programmable Position Presets for improved workflow efficiency

·         Ergonomic Designs to enhance surgeon comfort and reduce fatigue

By providing exceptional positioning accuracy and stability, ophthalmic operating tables improve surgical precision, support advanced ophthalmic technologies, enhance patient safety, and optimize operating room efficiency across hospitals, clinics, and ambulatory surgery centers.

